{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κοίτ-η</b>, ἡ, <br /> (κεῖμαι) ={κοῖτος} 1, once in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.341 (variant{οἴκῳ})\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>bedstead,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 12.330.16, +others, Wilcken “Chr.” 244.3 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>], etc.; especially <b>marriage-bed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 804 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 17; οὐ γὰρ ἐκ μιᾶς κ. ἔβλαστον [prev. author] “fragment” 546; τᾶς ἀπλήστου κ. ἔρος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 152 (Lyric poetry), etc.; ἀνάνδρου κοίτας λέκτρον [prev. work] 436 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also πετρίνη κοίτη, of a cave, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 160 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τειρομέναν νοσερᾷ κ. on a sick-<b>bed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 132 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κοίταν δ᾽ ἔχει νέρθεν, of one dead, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1706 (Lyric poetry); κ. σκληρά 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 942d, 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “ὀξέων νούσων θεραπευτικόν” 1.1: _plural_, ἔννυχοι κ. 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.25; νυμφίδιοι κ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 249 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, of the sea, ἐν μεσημβριναῖς κοίταις.. εὕδοι πεσών [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 566 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the <b>bed</b> of a river, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Procopius Caesariensis Historicus “de Aedificiis” 5.5, 6th c.AD: Philoponus, Joannes Philosophus “in Aristotelis Physica commentaria - Comm. in Arist. Graeca” 586.21, 6th c.AD: Lydus, Joannes Laurentius Historicus “de Mensibus” 4.10. \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>lair</b> of a wild beast, <b>nest</b> of a bird, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 155 (Lyric poetry); χελιδόνων 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 16.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ποιεῖσθαι, of the spider, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 623a12 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the fish ἐξώκοιτος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 171.1. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>quarters</b>, τῶν φυλακιτῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 1007.14 (3rd c.BC),compare “PTeb.” 179 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; see infr. VI. <br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>pen, fold</b> for cattle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLips.” 118.15 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>act of going to bed</b>, τῆς κοίτης ὥρη <b>bed</b>-time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.10, 5.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τραπέζῃ καὶ κοίτῃ δέκεσθαι to entertain 'at <b>bed</b> and board', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage]\">Refs</a>]; τὴν σκηνὴν εἰς κ. διέλυον for <b>going to bed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.3.1 (but κεῖσθαι κοίταν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>to lie still</b> in death, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1494 (Lyric poetry)). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>lodging, entertainment,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTeb. 122.1 (1st c.BC), +others \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> of <b>sexual connexion</b>, κ. διδόναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Num.5.20, cf. LXX.Lev.18.20; κ. σπέρματος [prev. work] 15.16 \">LXX</a>]; κ. ἔχειν ἐκ.. to become pregnant by a man, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Rom.9.10 \">NT</a>]; in bad sense, <b>lasciviousness</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 13.13 (_plural_). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>parcel, lot</b> of land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PAmh.” 2.88.9 (2nd c.AD), “PRyl.” 168.9 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__VI</b></Level2> <b>chest, case</b>, or <b>basket</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 122, 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 76, “IG” 22.120.37,40, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 129.2, “PPetr.” 2p.10 (3rd c.BC, unless in signification 1.3), 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Ep.Sat.” 21; αἱ μυστικαὶ κ. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Phocion” 28. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2845","accentedUnicode":"κοίτη","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2749","matchingForm":"κεῖμαι","stepTransliteration":"keimai","gloss":"to lay/be appointed","_zh_tw_Gloss":"放","_es_Gloss":"poner/ser designado","_zh_Gloss":"放"},{"strongNumber":"G2846","matchingForm":"κοιτών","stepTransliteration":"koitōn","gloss":"bedroom/chamberlain","_zh_tw_Gloss":"臥室","_es_Gloss":"dormitorio/camarero","_zh_Gloss":"卧室"}],"shortDef":"(marriage) bed; conception; sexual immorality","mediumDef":"(marriage) bed; conception; sexual immorality <br /><b>a bed,</b> <ref='Luk.11.7'>Lk. 11:7</ref>; <b>the</b> conjugal <b>bed,</b> <ref='Heb.13.4'>Heb. 13:4;</ref> <i>metonymy</i> <b>sexual intercourse, concubitus;</b> hence, <b>lewdness, whoredom, chambering,</b> <ref='Rom.13.13'>Rom. 13:13;</ref> in NT <b>conception,</b> <ref='Rom.9.10'>Rom. 9:10</ref>*","stepGloss":"bed","stepTransliteration":"koitē","count":4,"_es_Definition":"cama, lecho ; relaciones matrimoniales (HEB.13:4) ; semen ; inmoralidad sexual (ROM.13:13) ; concebir (ROM.9:10)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 床<br> 1a) 一般的床 (路 11:7)<br> 1b) 婚姻床 (來 13:4)<br>2